The Pension Transitional Arrangement Department (PTAD) is partnering the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) and Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Offences Commission (ICPC) to combat pension syndicates, the Director, Parastatals Pension Department, PTAD, Mr. Kabiru Yusuf has said. Yusuf, who spoke with reporters in Lagos, said there is a syndicate that have its tentacles in the public service departments, adding that the department is employing techonology to solve the problem.   ‘Pension fund hit N13.61tr in January’     Pension complaints and solutions     Return Head of Service, Perm Secs, AGF to CPS, says NUP   He said the criminals are using every instrument at their disposal  to hide their activities from the public. He said the PTAD is not surprised at the high-level resistance by those who have been draining the federal pension funds for decades.